  "timeboxMinutes": 25,
  "prompt": "During an incident, the transactions endpoint sometimes returns temporary 500 errors.\n\nWrite `fetch_all_transactions(base_url, token)`. Fetch every transaction from `GET {base_url}/v1/transactions`, always including `broken=1` in the query params. Retry 5xx responses for the same page with bounded exponential backoff, then continue pagination after the page succeeds.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `list[dict]`.\n- Each dict should be one transaction object from the API, unchanged.\n- Preserve API order.\n- Return `[]` if there are no transactions.\n\nTransaction shape:\n\n```python\n{\"id\": \"txn_001\", \"employee_id\": \"emp_001\", \"card_id\": \"card_001\", \"merchant\": \"United\", \"amount_cents\": 120000, \"category\": \"travel\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-01T12:00:00Z\"}\n```\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET {base_url}/v1/transactions` requires the bearer auth header.\n- Use params like `{\"limit\": 20, \"broken\": 1, \"cursor\": cursor}`.\n- Success response: `{\"data\": [...], \"next_cursor\": \"...\" | None}`.\n- Retry `status_code >= 500`. Treat 4xx as a real error.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- Do not omit `broken=1`; hidden tests require it.\n- Retry the same cursor after a 5xx. Do not advance the cursor on a failed response.\n- Reset your retry/backoff logic after a successful page.\n- Do not duplicate transactions after a retry.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: required query flag, bounded retry, later-page failures, pagination, and no duplicates.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "fetchAllTransactions",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "any"
      }
    }
  },
